  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6599.67 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-14.8B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+21.5B), dealers are currently in moderate buying mode as spot approaches the amplifying zone below. The PIN regime with 24.9B total GEX suggests dealers will aggressively buy any dip toward 6590 and sell strength above 6605, creating a tight 15-point trading range. Key inflection point is the GEX flip at 6622 - any sustained break above shifts dealers from stabilizing to amplifying mode.\n\nWatch 6590 as the critical support (dealers become heavy buyers) and 6605-6610 as resistance (dealer selling intensifies). The recent GEX surge and wall break events indicate heightened dealer hedging activity around these levels.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect choppy range-bound action between 6590-6610 with strong reversals at both ends.",
